trend_summary: Settlements gradually expand from the central corridor, replacing forest and fields with housing and light industry. Roads multiply, tightening the street grid, yet broad green tracts persist. Overall growth is steady rather than explosive, yielding a moderately built, still-green landscape.
notable_changes: Progressive residential infill north and south of the main arterial axis.
Clearing of western forest patches for new housing subdivisions.
Emergence of light-industrial/commercial blocks in the north-east sector.
Construction of additional secondary roads and junctions, densifying the network.
Gradual shrinkage of open farmland; some marginal plots transition back to woodland.
